    "narrative": "Our daily optimization for Ghost Ride the WHIP leans heavily into matchup exploitation today, specifically highlighting **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **Jose Caballero** (72.91) as our primary drivers. **Mickey Moniak** benefits immensely from a favorable encounter with Randy V\u00e1squez, with the model identifying a massive 14% platoon edge that vaults him to the top of our output. Similarly, **Jose Caballero** is a priority start despite his #8 hole in the lineup; his 86% stolen base efficiency against the slower delivery of Springs creates a massive ceiling in our most scarce category. **Giancarlo Stanton** (68.81) rounds out our elite tier, as the park factors and a strong 14% SP skill differential against a middling lefty in Springs make him a high-leverage play for power.\n\nConversely, our primary concerns center on the top of the order where **Gabriel Moreno** (43.43) and **Corbin Carroll** (56.89) are forced to contend with Nolan McLean, an elite arm sporting a 3.04 xERA. While **Corbin Carroll** remains a start due to his inherent speed upside, his score is suppressed by the difficult SP matchup. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (53.94) is another borderline play; while he benefits from a 5% wind boost, the 15% platoon penalty against Anthony Kay keeps his efficiency squarely in the middle of our range. Looking at our bench, **Zach McKinstry** (48.81) represents the final inclusion over potential alternatives, though he remains a marginal play as the model favors his steady floor over the riskier profiles currently held by **Seiya Suzuki** or **Trevor Story**. We are monitoring lineup confirmations closely for **Gabriel Moreno**, **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Kyle Karros**, **Corbin Carroll**, and **Mickey Moniak**; any drop in their projected batting order will necessitate a reassessment of our daily efficiency scores, particularly for those hovering near the 40-point threshold.",
